nuum limit constrains the couplings to\nlie in a three-dimensional subspace, whose equation is explicitly given. We\nemphasize throughout the difference between scheme-dependent and\nscheme-independent results, and provide several examples of the fact that only\ndimensionless couplings can have \"universal\" behavior.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 May 2008 17:07:43 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 20 May 2008 15:03:45 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 28 May 2008 12:53:04 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 9 Jan 2009 13:29:23 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Tue, 27 Aug 2013 14:25:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2013-08-28"}
