h can be plausibly modeled as moderately embedded\nintermediate-mass ZAMS stars. Our results strengthen the suggestion that the\ncentral core in Mol160/IRAS23385+6053 is a massive YSO actively accreting from\nits circumstellar envelope and which did not yet begin hydrogen fusion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 19 May 2008 19:24:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 19 May 2008 20:55:59 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
