 ISM relationship. Upper\nlimits for 6379 and 6613 DIBs show that these are at least a factor of seven\nweaker. Therefore, the Galactic DIB-reddening relation does not seem to hold in\nM100, although the lower gas-to-dust ratio may further reduce this discrepancy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 May 2008 09:27:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
