 time interval. The policy implications of the above empirical results\nconcern the economic clusters arising in the presence of Marshallian\nexternalities and the relationships between trade barriers, R&D incentives and\ngrowth that must be accounted in elaborating a cluster-promotion policy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 20 May 2008 13:06:30 GMT"}],"update_date":"2010-03-16"}
